<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-241-473  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 241 473.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Jan 9 1989 v11 n2 p22(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hard disk voice coil positioning technology comes of age. (TechTalk) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gibson, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Voice coil positioning technology in hard disks is now matureenough to be applied without fear.andP;  The technology is well knownand has a long history, but until recently, it was risky.andP;  Storiesabout lost servo platters and catastrophic positioner failures arecommon.andP;  Voice coil positioning involves using a coil of wiresuspended within a strong magnetic field.andP;  A set of read-writeheads is attached to the coil of wire and can be moved over thehard disk platter by running electricity through the coil.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Hard DiskDisk DrivesTechnology.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>